                             16:==================================================================== */                                                                                                          
                             17:package org.apache.poi.hssf.record;                                                                                                                                              
                             18:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             19:import java.io.InputStream;                                                                                                                                                      
                             20:import java.security.GeneralSecurityException;                                                                                                                                   
                             21:import java.util.ArrayList;                                                                                                                                                      
                             22:import java.util.List;                                                                                                                                                           
                             23:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             24:import org.apache.poi.EncryptedDocumentException;                                                                                                                                
                             25:import org.apache.poi.hssf.eventusermodel.HSSFEventFactory;                                                                                                                      
                             26:import org.apache.poi.hssf.eventusermodel.HSSFListener;                                                                                                                          
                             27:import org.apache.poi.hssf.record.crypto.Biff8EncryptionKey;                                                                                                                     
                             28:import org.apache.poi.poifs.crypt.Decryptor;                                                                                                                                     
                             29:import org.apache.poi.poifs.crypt.EncryptionInfo;                                                                                                                                
                             30:import org.apache.poi.util.RecordFormatException;                                                                                                                                
                             31:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             32:/**                                                                                                                                                                              
                             33: * A stream based way to get at complete records, with                                                                                                                           
                             34: * as low a memory footprint as possible.                                                                                                                                        
                             35: * This handles reading from a RecordInputStream, turning                                                                                                                        
                             36: * the data into full records, processing continue records                                                                                                                       
                             37: * etc.                                                                                                                                                                          
                             38: * Most users should use {@link HSSFEventFactory} /                                                                                                                              
                             39: * {@link HSSFListener} and have new records pushed to                                                                                                                           
                             40: * them, but this does allow for a "pull" style of coding.                                                                                                                       
                             41: */                                                                                                                                                                              
                             42:public final class RecordFactoryInputStream {                                                                                                                                    
                             43:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             44:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             45:     * Keeps track of the sizes of the initial records up to and including {@link FilePassRecord}                                                                                
                             46:     * Needed for protected files because each byte is encrypted with respect to its absolute                                                                                    
                             47:     * position from the start of the stream.                                                                                                                                    
                             48:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             49:    private static final class StreamEncryptionInfo {                                                                                                                            
                             50:        private final int _initialRecordsSize;                                                                                                                                   
                             51:        private final FilePassRecord _filePassRec;                                                                                                                               
                             52:        private final Record _lastRecord;                                                                                                                                        
                             53:        private final boolean _hasBOFRecord;                                                                                                                                     
                             54:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             55:        public StreamEncryptionInfo(RecordInputStream rs, List<org.apache.poi.hssf.record.Record> outputRecs) {                                                                  
                             56:            Record rec;                                                                                                                                                          
                             57:            rs.nextRecord();                                                                                                                                                     
                             58:            int recSize = 4 + rs.remaining();                                                                                                                                    
                             59:            rec = RecordFactory.createSingleRecord(rs);                                                                                                                          
                             60:            outputRecs.add(rec);                                                                                                                                                 
                             61:            FilePassRecord fpr = null;                                                                                                                                           
                             62:            if (rec instanceof BOFRecord) {                                                                                                                                      
                             63:                _hasBOFRecord = true;                                                                                                                                            
                             64:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             65:                // Fetch the next record, and see if it indicates whether                                                                                                        
                             66:                //  the document is encrypted or not                                                                                                                             
                             67:                if (rs.hasNextRecord()) {                                                                                                                                        
                             68:                    rs.nextRecord();                                                                                                                                             
                             69:                    rec = RecordFactory.createSingleRecord(rs);                                                                                                                  
                             70:                    recSize += rec.getRecordSize();                                                                                                                              
                             71:                    outputRecs.add(rec);                                                                                                                                         
                             72:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             73:                    // Encrypted is normally BOF then FILEPASS                                                                                                                   
                             74:                    // May sometimes be BOF, WRITEPROTECT, FILEPASS                                                                                                              
                             75:                    if (rec instanceof WriteProtectRecord && rs.hasNextRecord()) {                                                                                               
                             76:                   rs.nextRecord();                                                                                                                                              
                             77:                   rec = RecordFactory.createSingleRecord(rs);                                                                                                                   
                             78:                   recSize += rec.getRecordSize();                                                                                                                               
                             79:                   outputRecs.add(rec);                                                                                                                                          
                             80:                    }                                                                                                                                                            
                             81:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             82:                    // If it's a FILEPASS, track it specifically                                                                                                                 
                             83:                    if (rec instanceof FilePassRecord) {                                                                                                                         
                             84:                        fpr = (FilePassRecord) rec;                                                                                                                              
                             85:                    }                                                                                                                                                            
                             86:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             87:                    // workbook not encrypted (typical case)                                                                                                                     
                             88:                    if (rec instanceof EOFRecord) {                                                                                                                              
                             89:                        // A workbook stream is never empty, so crash instead                                                                                                    
                             90:                        // of trying to keep track of nesting level                                                                                                              
                             91:                        throw new IllegalStateException("Nothing between BOF and EOF");                                                                                          
                             92:                    }                                                                                                                                                            
                             93:                }                                                                                                                                                                
                             94:            } else {                                                                                                                                                             
                             95:                // Invalid in a normal workbook stream.                                                                                                                          
                             96:                // However, some test cases work on sub-sections of                                                                                                              
                             97:                // the workbook stream that do not begin with BOF                                                                                                                
                             98:                _hasBOFRecord = false;                                                                                                                                           
                             99:            }                                                                                                                                                                    
                             100:            _initialRecordsSize = recSize;                                                                                                                                      
                             101:            _filePassRec = fpr;                                                                                                                                                 
                             102:            _lastRecord = rec;                                                                                                                                                  
                             103:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             104:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             105:        @SuppressWarnings({"squid:S2068"})                                                                                                                                      
                             106:        public RecordInputStream createDecryptingStream(InputStream original) {                                                                                                 
                             107:            String userPassword = Biff8EncryptionKey.getCurrentUserPassword();                                                                                                  
                             108:            if (userPassword == null) {                                                                                                                                         
                             109:                userPassword = Decryptor.DEFAULT_PASSWORD;                                                                                                                      
                             110:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             111:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             112:            EncryptionInfo info = _filePassRec.getEncryptionInfo();                                                                                                             
                             113:            try {                                                                                                                                                               
                             114:                if (!info.getDecryptor().verifyPassword(userPassword)) {                                                                                                        
                             115:                    throw new EncryptedDocumentException(                                                                                                                       
                             116:                            (Decryptor.DEFAULT_PASSWORD.equals(userPassword) ? "Default" : "Supplied")                                                                          
                             117:                            + " password is invalid for salt/verifier/verifierHash");                                                                                           
                             118:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             119:            } catch (GeneralSecurityException e) {                                                                                                                              
                             120:                throw new EncryptedDocumentException(e);                                                                                                                        
                             121:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             122:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             123:            return new RecordInputStream(original, info, _initialRecordsSize);                                                                                                  
                             124:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             125:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             126:        public boolean hasEncryption() {                                                                                                                                        
                             127:            return _filePassRec != null;                                                                                                                                        
                             128:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             129:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             130:        /**                                                                                                                                                                     
                             131:         * @return last record scanned while looking for encryption info.                                                                                                       
                             132:         * This will typically be the first or second record read. Possibly <code>null</code>                                                                                   
                             133:         * if stream was empty                                                                                                                                                  
                             134:         */                                                                                                                                                                     
                             135:        public Record getLastRecord() {                                                                                                                                         
                             136:            return _lastRecord;                                                                                                                                                 
                             137:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             138:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             139:        /**                                                                                                                                                                     
                             140:         * <code>false</code> in some test cases                                                                                                                                
                             141:         */                                                                                                                                                                     
                             142:        public boolean hasBOFRecord() {                                                                                                                                         
                             143:            return _hasBOFRecord;                                                                                                                                               
                             144:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             145:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             146:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             147:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             148:    private final RecordInputStream _recStream;                                                                                                                                 
                             149:    private final boolean _shouldIncludeContinueRecords;                                                                                                                        
                             150:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             151:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             152:     * Temporarily stores a group of {@link Record}s, for future return by {@link #nextRecord()}.                                                                               
                             153:     * This is used at the start of the workbook stream, and also when the most recently read                                                                                   
                             154:     * underlying record is a {@link MulRKRecord}                                                                                                                               
                             155:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             156:    private Record[] _unreadRecordBuffer;                                                                                                                                       
                             157:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             158:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             159:     * used to help iterating over the unread records                                                                                                                           
                             160:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             161:    private int _unreadRecordIndex = -1;                                                                                                                                        
                             162:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             163:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             164:     * The most recent record that we gave to the user                                                                                                                          
                             165:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             166:    private Record _lastRecord;                                                                                                                                                 
                             167:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             168:     * The most recent DrawingRecord seen                                                                                                                                       
                             169:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             170:    private DrawingRecord _lastDrawingRecord = new DrawingRecord();                                                                                                             
                             171:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             172:    private int _bofDepth;                                                                                                                                                      
                             173:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             174:    private boolean _lastRecordWasEOFLevelZero;                                                                                                                                 
                             175:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             176:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             177:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             178:     * @param in the InputStream to read from                                                                                                                                   
                             179:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             180:     * @param shouldIncludeContinueRecords caller can pass <code>false</code> if loose                                                                                          
                             181:     * {@link ContinueRecord}s should be skipped (this is sometimes useful in event based                                                                                       
                             182:     * processing).                                                                                                                                                             
                             183:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             184:    public RecordFactoryInputStream(InputStream in, boolean shouldIncludeContinueRecords) {                                                                                     
                             185:        RecordInputStream rs = new RecordInputStream(in);                                                                                                                       
                             186:        List<org.apache.poi.hssf.record.Record> records = new ArrayList<>();                                                                                                    
                             187:        StreamEncryptionInfo sei = new StreamEncryptionInfo(rs, records);                                                                                                       
                             188:        if (sei.hasEncryption()) {                                                                                                                                              
                             189:            rs = sei.createDecryptingStream(in);                                                                                                                                
                             190:        } else {                                                                                                                                                                
                             191:            // typical case - non-encrypted stream                                                                                                                              
                             192:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             193:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             194:        if (!records.isEmpty()) {                                                                                                                                               
                             195:            _unreadRecordBuffer = new Record[records.size()];                                                                                                                   
                             196:            records.toArray(_unreadRecordBuffer);                                                                                                                               
                             197:            _unreadRecordIndex =0;                                                                                                                                              
                             198:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             199:        _recStream = rs;                                                                                                                                                        
                             200:        _shouldIncludeContinueRecords = shouldIncludeContinueRecords;                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordFactoryInputStream.java:200-260                                                                                                  
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             200:        _shouldIncludeContinueRecords = shouldIncludeContinueRecords;                                                                                                           
                             201:        _lastRecord = sei.getLastRecord();                                                                                                                                      
                             202:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             203:        /*                                                                                                                                                                      
                             204:        * How to recognise end of stream?                                                                                                                                       
                             205:        * In the best case, the underlying input stream (in) ends just after the last EOF record                                                                                
                             206:        * Usually however, the stream is padded with an arbitrary byte count.  Excel and most apps                                                                              
                             207:        * reliably use zeros for padding and if this were always the case, this code could just                                                                                 
                             208:        * skip all the (zero sized) records with sid==0.  However, bug 46987 shows a file with                                                                                  
                             209:        * non-zero padding that is read OK by Excel (Excel also fixes the padding).                                                                                             
                             210:        *                                                                                                                                                                       
                             211:        * So to properly detect the workbook end of stream, this code has to identify the last                                                                                  
                             212:        * EOF record.  This is not so easy because the worbook bof+eof pair do not bracket the                                                                                  
                             213:        * whole stream.  The worksheets follow the workbook, but it is not easy to tell how many                                                                                
                             214:        * sheet sub-streams should be present.  Hence we are looking for an EOF record that is not                                                                              
                             215:        * immediately followed by a BOF record.  One extra complication is that bof+eof sub-                                                                                    
                             216:        * streams can be nested within worksheet streams and it's not clear in these cases what                                                                                 
                             217:        * record might follow any EOF record.  So we also need to keep track of the bof/eof                                                                                     
                             218:        * nesting level.                                                                                                                                                        
                             219:        */                                                                                                                                                                      
                             220:        _bofDepth = sei.hasBOFRecord() ? 1 : 0;                                                                                                                                 
                             221:        _lastRecordWasEOFLevelZero = false;                                                                                                                                     
                             222:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             223:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             224:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             225:     * @return the next (complete) record from the stream, or null if there are no more.                                                                                        
                             226:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             227:    public Record nextRecord() {                                                                                                                                                
                             228:        Record r;                                                                                                                                                               
                             229:        r = getNextUnreadRecord();                                                                                                                                              
                             230:        if (r != null) {                                                                                                                                                        
                             231:            // found an unread record                                                                                                                                           
                             232:            return r;                                                                                                                                                           
                             233:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             234:        while (true) {                                                                                                                                                          
                             235:            if (!_recStream.hasNextRecord()) {                                                                                                                                  
                             236:                // recStream is exhausted;                                                                                                                                      
                             237:                return null;                                                                                                                                                    
                             238:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             239:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             240:            if (_lastRecordWasEOFLevelZero) {                                                                                                                                   
                             241:                // Potential place for ending the workbook stream                                                                                                               
                             242:                // Check that the next record is not BOFRecord(0x0809)                                                                                                          
                             243:                // Normally the input stream contains only zero padding after the last EOFRecord,                                                                               
                             244:                // but bug 46987 and 48068 suggests that the padding may be garbage.                                                                                            
                             245:                // This code relies on the padding bytes not starting with BOFRecord.sid                                                                                        
                             246:                if (_recStream.getNextSid() != BOFRecord.sid) {                                                                                                                 
                             247:                    return null;                                                                                                                                                
                             248:                }                                                                                                                                                               
                             249:                // else - another sheet substream starting here                                                                                                                 
                             250:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             251:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             252:            // step underlying RecordInputStream to the next record                                                                                                             
                             253:            _recStream.nextRecord();                                                                                                                                            
                             254:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             255:            r = readNextRecord();                                                                                                                                               
                             256:            if (r == null) {                                                                                                                                                    
                             257:                // some record types may get skipped (e.g. DBCellRecord and ContinueRecord)                                                                                     
                             258:                continue;                                                                                                                                                       
                             259:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             260:            return r;                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>

                             180:    public static List<org.apache.poi.hssf.record.Record> createRecords(InputStream in) throws RecordFormatException {                                                          
                             181:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             182:        List<org.apache.poi.hssf.record.Record> records = new ArrayList<>(NUM_RECORDS);                                                                                         
                             183:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             184:        RecordFactoryInputStream recStream = new RecordFactoryInputStream(in, true);                                                                                            
                             185:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             186:        Record record;                                                                                                                                                          
                             187:        while ((record = recStream.nextRecord())!=null) {                                                                                                                       
                             188:            records.add(record);                                                                                                                                                
                             189:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             190:            IOUtils.safelyAllocateCheck(records.size(), MAX_NUMBER_OF_RECORDS);                                                                                                 
                             191:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             192:

                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordInputStream.java:377-382                                                                                                         
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             377:    private String readStringCommon(int requestedLength, boolean pIsCompressedEncoding) {                                                                                       
                             378:        // Sanity check to detect garbage string lengths                                                                                                                        
                             379:        if (requestedLength < 0 || requestedLength > 0x100000) { // 16 million chars?                                                                                           
                             380:            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Bad requested string length (" + requestedLength + ")");                                                                        
                             381:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             382:        char[] buf = new char[requestedLength];                                                                                                                                 
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             </code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Summary of Root Cause                                                                                                                                                            
                                The `readStringCommon` method in `RecordInputStream` (and potentially other parsing routines in the same class) throws `IllegalArgumentException` to signal                      
                             malformed or out-of-bounds string lengths (and other parsing anomalies).  This is inconsistent with the rest of POIs HSSF parsing framework, which uses the                        
                             unchecked `org.apache.poi.util.RecordFormatException` to signal recordformat issues.  The fuzzer harness treats any unchecked exception as a crash, so we need to                  
                             unify on the POI parsing exception.                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. High-Level Patch Plan                                                                                                                                                            
                                a. In `RecordInputStream.java`, replace *all* `throw new IllegalArgumentException(  )` calls that guard against parsing errors with `RecordFormatException`                     
                             (either via `throw new RecordFormatException(...)` or `RecordFormatException.check(...)`).                                                                                          
                                b. Specifically in `readStringCommon`, change the guard from:                                                                                                                    
                                     if (requestedLength < 0 || requestedLength > 0x100000) {                                                                                                                    
                                         throw new IllegalArgumentException("Bad requested string length (" + requestedLength + ")");                                                                            
                                     }                                                                                                                                                                           
                                   to:                                                                                                                                                                           
                                     RecordFormatException.check(                                                                                                                                                
                                         requestedLength >= 0 && requestedLength <= 0x100000,                                                                                                                    
                                         "Bad requested string length (" + requestedLength + ")"                                                                                                                 
                                     );                                                                                                                                                                          
                                c. Search the rest of `RecordInputStream` for any other `throw new IllegalArgumentException(...)` (for example, bad compression flags or other recordparsing                    
                             invariants) and replace them with `RecordFormatException`.                                                                                                                          
                                d. Ensure the class imports `org.apache.poi.util.RecordFormatException` and remove any semantically redundant supporting code (no need to catch or reimport                     
                             `IllegalArgumentException`).                                                                                                                                                        
                                e. Do *not* modify harness code, external libraries, or test code.  Upstream API signatures remain unchanged: methods will still throw unchecked exceptions on                   
                             format errors, but now uniformly as `RecordFormatException`.                                                                                                                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Detailed Steps                                                                                                                                                                   
                                1. Open `poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordInputStream.java`.                                                                                                   
                                2. At the top imports (lines ~2033), verify that `import org.apache.poi.util.RecordFormatException;` is present.                                                                
                                3. Locate the `readStringCommon(int requestedLength, boolean pIsCompressedEncoding)` method.                                                                                     
                                4. Replace lines 379381:                                                                                                                                                        
                                      if (requestedLength < 0 || requestedLength > 0x100000) {                                                                                                                   
                                          throw new IllegalArgumentException("Bad requested string length (" + requestedLength + ")");                                                                           
                                      }                                                                                                                                                                          
                                   with:                                                                                                                                                                         
                                      RecordFormatException.check(                                                                                                                                               
                                          requestedLength >= 0 && requestedLength <= 0x100000,                                                                                                                   
                                          "Bad requested string length (" + requestedLength + ")"                                                                                                                
                                      );                                                                                                                                                                         
                                5. Search the same file for other occurrences of `throw new IllegalArgumentException(`, for example in methods that validate options flags or header fields.                     
                             For each occurrence:                                                                                                                                                                
                                   - Replace `throw new IllegalArgumentException(msg)` with `throw new RecordFormatException(msg)`, or use `RecordFormatException.check(...)` if the exception                   
                             arises from a boolean assertion.                                                                                                                                                    
                                6. Rebuild and rerun the original POIHSSFFuzzer fuzz harness.  The fuzzer will still traverse the same code paths but, on encountering an invalid length or                      
                             flag, will now throw a `RecordFormatException` instead of an `IllegalArgumentException`.  Upstream recordfactory code already declares `throws                                     
                             RecordFormatException` and will propagate it in a consistent manner.                                                                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Why This Fix Preserves Functionality                                                                                                                                             
                                - We are not altering the control flow or logic of parsingonly the type of exception raised on invariant violations.                                                            
                                - `RecordFormatException` is unchecked (subclass of `RuntimeException`), so we are not changing method signatures or requiring new catch clauses unless callers                  
                             specifically want to handle format errors.                                                                                                                                          
                                - Upstream callers in `RecordFactory` and `HSSFEventFactory` already expect and propagate `RecordFormatException` on parse errors; this change simply unifies                    
                             all parsingerror signals under that type.                                                                                                                                          
                                - No changes to harness or tests are required; existing unit tests will continue to pass (invalid records will still produce a runtime exception), and the                       
                             fuzzer will no longer see `IllegalArgumentException` crashes but will instead report `RecordFormatException`, which can be recognized as standard POI parsingerror                 
                             behavior.                                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Side Effects & Mitigations                                                                                                                                                       
                                - Any client code that *explicitly* caught `IllegalArgumentException` from `RecordInputStream` will now miss those exceptions and may instead see an uncaught                    
                             `RecordFormatException`.  Mitigation: We audited `RecordInputStream` and found no catch blocks that selectively handled `IllegalArgumentException`; most HSSF entry                 
                             points either declare `throws RecordFormatException` or let unchecked exceptions bubble to the caller.                                                                              
                                - This does not swallow errors; malformed records still cause a runtime exception and abort parsing, which is POIs intended semantics.                                          
                                - We avoid catching exceptions at a higher level (e.g., in `nextRecord()`), so we do not inadvertently hide genuine parsing bugs or corruptfile conditions from                 
                             both application users and the fuzzer harness.                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             6. Optional Follow-On                                                                                                                                                               
                                - If the fuzzer harness still flags `RecordFormatException` as a crash, consider coordinating with the fuzz-harness maintainers to whitelist                                     
                             `RecordFormatException` as a non-crash parsingerror type.  This does *not* require any changes to POIs codebase.                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             ===Evaluation End===
