                             18:package org.apache.poi.hssf.record.common;                                                                                                                                       
                             19:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             20:import java.util.ArrayList;                                                                                                                                                      
                             21:import java.util.Collections;                                                                                                                                                    
                             22:import java.util.Iterator;                                                                                                                                                       
                             23:import java.util.List;                                                                                                                                                           
                             24:import java.util.Map;                                                                                                                                                            
                             25:import java.util.Objects;                                                                                                                                                        
                             26:import java.util.Spliterator;                                                                                                                                                    
                             27:import java.util.function.Supplier;                                                                                                                                              
                             28:import java.util.stream.Collectors;                                                                                                                                              
                             29:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             30:import org.apache.logging.log4j.Logger;                                                                                                                                          
                             31:import org.apache.poi.logging.PoiLogManager;                                                                                                                                     
                             32:import org.apache.poi.common.Duplicatable;                                                                                                                                       
                             33:import org.apache.poi.common.usermodel.GenericRecord;                                                                                                                            
                             34:import org.apache.poi.hssf.record.RecordInputStream;                                                                                                                             
                             35:import org.apache.poi.hssf.record.cont.ContinuableRecordInput;                                                                                                                   
                             36:import org.apache.poi.hssf.record.cont.ContinuableRecordOutput;                                                                                                                  
                             37:import org.apache.poi.util.BitField;                                                                                                                                             
                             38:import org.apache.poi.util.BitFieldFactory;                                                                                                                                      
                             39:import org.apache.poi.util.GenericRecordUtil;                                                                                                                                    
                             40:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             41:import static org.apache.logging.log4j.util.Unbox.box;                                                                                                                           
                             42:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             43:/**                                                                                                                                                                              
                             44: * Unicode String - just standard fields that are in several records.                                                                                                            
                             45: * It is considered more desirable than repeating it in all of them.<p>                                                                                                          
                             46: * This is often called a XLUnicodeRichExtendedString in MS documentation.                                                                                                       
                             47: */                                                                                                                                                                              
                             48:public class UnicodeString implements Comparable<UnicodeString>, Duplicatable, GenericRecord {                                                                                   
                             49:    private static final Logger LOG = PoiLogManager.getLogger(UnicodeString.class);                                                                                              
                             50:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             51:    private static final BitField highByte  = BitFieldFactory.getInstance(0x1);                                                                                                  
                             52:    // 0x2 is reserved                                                                                                                                                           
                             53:    private static final BitField extBit    = BitFieldFactory.getInstance(0x4);                                                                                                  
                             54:    private static final BitField richText  = BitFieldFactory.getInstance(0x8);                                                                                                  
                             55:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             56:    private short             field_1_charCount;                                                                                                                                 
                             57:    private byte              field_2_optionflags;                                                                                                                               
                             58:    private String            field_3_string;                                                                                                                                    
                             59:    private List<FormatRun>   field_4_format_runs;                                                                                                                               
                             60:    private ExtRst            field_5_ext_rst;                                                                                                                                   
                             61:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             62:    private UnicodeString(UnicodeString other) {                                                                                                                                 
                             63:        field_1_charCount = other.field_1_charCount;                                                                                                                             
                             64:        field_2_optionflags = other.field_2_optionflags;                                                                                                                         
                             65:        field_3_string = other.field_3_string;                                                                                                                                   
                             66:        field_4_format_runs =  (other.field_4_format_runs == null) ? null :                                                                                                      
                             67:            other.field_4_format_runs.stream().map(FormatRun::new).collect(Collectors.toList());                                                                                 
                             68:        field_5_ext_rst = (other.field_5_ext_rst == null) ? null : other.field_5_ext_rst.copy();                                                                                 
                             69:    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                             70:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             71:    public UnicodeString(String str) {                                                                                                                                           
                             72:      setString(str);                                                                                                                                                            
                             73:    }                                                                                                                                                                            
                             74:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             75:    /**                                                                                                                                                                          
                             76:     * construct a unicode string record and fill its fields, ID is ignored                                                                                                      
                             77:     * @param in the RecordInputStream to read the record from                                                                                                                   
                             78:     */                                                                                                                                                                          
                             79:    public UnicodeString(RecordInputStream in) {                                                                                                                                 
                             80:        field_1_charCount   = in.readShort();                                                                                                                                    
                             81:        field_2_optionflags = in.readByte();                                                                                                                                     
                             82:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             83:        int runCount = 0;                                                                                                                                                        
                             84:        int extensionLength = 0;                                                                                                                                                 
                             85:        //Read the number of rich runs if rich text.                                                                                                                             
                             86:        if (isRichText()) {                                                                                                                                                      
                             87:            runCount = in.readShort();                                                                                                                                           
                             88:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             89:        //Read the size of extended data if present.                                                                                                                             
                             90:        if (isExtendedText()) {                                                                                                                                                  
                             91:            extensionLength = in.readInt();                                                                                                                                      
                             92:        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                             93:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             94:        boolean isCompressed = ((field_2_optionflags & 1) == 0);                                                                                                                 
                             95:        int cc = getCharCount();                                                                                                                                                 
                             96:        field_3_string = (isCompressed) ? in.readCompressedUnicode(cc) : in.readUnicodeLEString(cc);                                                                             
                             97:                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             98:        if (isRichText() && (runCount > 0)) {                                                                                                                                    
                             99:          field_4_format_runs = new ArrayList<>(runCount);                                                                                                                       
                             100:          for (int i=0;i<runCount;i++) {                                                                                                                                        
                             101:            field_4_format_runs.add(new FormatRun(in));                                                                                                                         
                             102:          }                                                                                                                                                                     
                             103:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             104:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             105:        if (isExtendedText() && (extensionLength > 0)) {                                                                                                                        
                             106:          field_5_ext_rst = new ExtRst(new ContinuableRecordInput(in), extensionLength);                                                                                        
                             107:          if(field_5_ext_rst.getDataSize()+4 != extensionLength) {                                                                                                              
                             108:              LOG.atWarn().log("ExtRst was supposed to be {} bytes long, but seems to actually be {}", box(extensionLength),box(field_5_ext_rst.getDataSize() +                 
                             4));                                                                                                                                                                                
                             109:          }                                                                                                                                                                     
                             110:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             111:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             112:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             113:    public int hashCode() {                                                                                                                                                     
                             114:        return Objects.hash(field_1_charCount, field_3_string);                                                                                                                 
                             115:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             116:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             117:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             118:     * Our handling of equals is inconsistent with compareTo.  The trouble is because we don't truly understand                                                                 
                             119:     * rich text fields, yet it's difficult to make a sound comparison.                                                                                                         
                             120:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             121:     * @param o     The object to compare.                                                                                                                                      
                             122:     * @return      true if the object is actually equal.                                                                                                                       
                             123:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             124:    public boolean equals(Object o)                                                                                                                                             
                             125:    {                                                                                                                                                                           
                             126:        if (!(o instanceof UnicodeString)) {                                                                                                                                    
                             127:            return false;                                                                                                                                                       
                             128:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             129:        UnicodeString other = (UnicodeString) o;                                                                                                                                
                             130:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             131:        //OK lets do this in stages to return quickly, first check the actual string                                                                                            
                             132:        if (field_1_charCount != other.field_1_charCount                                                                                                                        
                             133:                || field_2_optionflags != other.field_2_optionflags                                                                                                             
                             134:                || !field_3_string.equals(other.field_3_string)) {                                                                                                              
                             135:            return false;                                                                                                                                                       
                             136:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             137:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             138:        //OK string appears to be equal but now lets compare formatting runs                                                                                                    
                             139:        if (field_4_format_runs == null) {                                                                                                                                      
                             140:            // Strings are equal, and there are not formatting runs.                                                                                                            
                             141:            return (other.field_4_format_runs == null);                                                                                                                         
                             142:        } else if (other.field_4_format_runs == null) {                                                                                                                         
                             143:            // Strings are equal, but one or the other has formatting runs                                                                                                      
                             144:            return false;                                                                                                                                                       
                             145:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             146:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             147:        //Strings are equal, so now compare formatting runs.                                                                                                                    
                             148:        int size = field_4_format_runs.size();                                                                                                                                  
                             149:        if (size != other.field_4_format_runs.size()) {                                                                                                                         
                             150:            return false;                                                                                                                                                       
                             151:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             152:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             153:        for (int i=0;i<size;i++) {                                                                                                                                              
                             154:            FormatRun run1 = field_4_format_runs.get(i);                                                                                                                        
                             155:            FormatRun run2 = other.field_4_format_runs.get(i);                                                                                                                  
                             156:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             157:            if (!run1.equals(run2)) {                                                                                                                                           
                             158:                return false;                                                                                                                                                   
                             159:            }                                                                                                                                                                   
                             160:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             161:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             162:        // Well the format runs are equal as well!, better check the ExtRst data                                                                                                
                             163:        if (field_5_ext_rst == null) {                                                                                                                                          
                             164:            return (other.field_5_ext_rst == null);                                                                                                                             
                             165:        } else if (other.field_5_ext_rst == null) {                                                                                                                             
                             166:            return false;                                                                                                                                                       
                             167:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             168:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             169:        return field_5_ext_rst.equals(other.field_5_ext_rst);                                                                                                                   
                             170:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             171:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             172:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             173:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             174:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             175:     * get the number of characters in the string,                                                                                                                              
                             176:     *  as an un-wrapped int                                                                                                                                                    
                             177:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             178:     * @return number of characters                                                                                                                                             
                             179:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             180:    public int getCharCount() {                                                                                                                                                 
                             181:        if(field_1_charCount < 0) {                                                                                                                                             
                             182:            return field_1_charCount + 65536;                                                                                                                                   
                             183:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             184:        return field_1_charCount;                                                                                                                                               
                             185:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             186:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             187:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             188:     * get the number of characters in the string,                                                                                                                              
                             189:     * wrapped as needed to fit within a short                                                                                                                                  
                             190:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             191:     * @return number of characters                                                                                                                                             
                             192:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             193:    public short getCharCountShort() {                                                                                                                                          
                             194:        return field_1_charCount;                                                                                                                                               
                             195:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             196:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             197:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             198:     * set the number of characters in the string                                                                                                                               
                             199:     * @param cc - number of characters                                                                                                                                         
                             200:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/usermodel/HSSFWorkbook.java:400-430                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             400:            names.add(name);                                                                                                                                                    
                             401:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             402:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             403:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             404:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             405:     * Companion to HSSFWorkbook(POIFSFileSystem), this constructs the                                                                                                          
                             406:     * POI filesystem around your {@link InputStream}, including all nodes.                                                                                                     
                             407:     * <p>This calls {@link #HSSFWorkbook(InputStream, boolean)} with                                                                                                           
                             408:     * preserve nodes set to true.                                                                                                                                              
                             409:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             410:     * @throws IOException if the stream cannot be read                                                                                                                         
                             411:     * @throws IllegalStateException a number of runtime exceptions can be thrown, especially if there are problems with the                                                    
                             412:     * input format                                                                                                                                                             
                             413:     * @see #HSSFWorkbook(InputStream, boolean)                                                                                                                                 
                             414:     * @see #HSSFWorkbook(POIFSFileSystem)                                                                                                                                      
                             415:     * @see POIFSFileSystem                                                                                                                                                     
                             416:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             417:    public HSSFWorkbook(InputStream s) throws IOException {                                                                                                                     
                             418:        this(s, true);                                                                                                                                                          
                             419:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             420:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             421:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             422:     * Companion to HSSFWorkbook(POIFSFileSystem), this constructs the                                                                                                          
                             423:     * POI filesystem around your {@link InputStream}.                                                                                                                          
                             424:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             425:     * @param s             the POI filesystem that contains the Workbook stream.                                                                                               
                             426:     * @param preserveNodes whether to preserve other nodes, such as                                                                                                            
                             427:     *                      macros.  This takes more memory, so only say yes if you                                                                                             
                             428:     *                      need to.                                                                                                                                            
                             429:     * @throws IOException if the stream cannot be read                                                                                                                         
                             430:     * @throws IllegalStateException a number of runtime exceptions can be thrown, especially if there are problems with the                                                    
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/usermodel/HSSFWorkbook.java:430-460                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             430:     * @throws IllegalStateException a number of runtime exceptions can be thrown, especially if there are problems with the                                                    
                             431:     * input format                                                                                                                                                             
                             432:     * @see POIFSFileSystem                                                                                                                                                     
                             433:     * @see #HSSFWorkbook(POIFSFileSystem)                                                                                                                                      
                             434:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             435:    @SuppressWarnings("resource")   // POIFSFileSystem always closes the stream                                                                                                 
                             436:    public HSSFWorkbook(InputStream s, boolean preserveNodes)                                                                                                                   
                             437:            throws IOException {                                                                                                                                                
                             438:        this(new POIFSFileSystem(s).getRoot(), preserveNodes);                                                                                                                  
                             439:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             440:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             441:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             442:     * used internally to set the workbook properties.                                                                                                                          
                             443:     */                                                                                                                                                                         
                             444:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             445:    private void setPropertiesFromWorkbook(InternalWorkbook book) {                                                                                                             
                             446:        this.workbook = book;                                                                                                                                                   
                             447:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             448:        // none currently                                                                                                                                                       
                             449:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             450:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             451:    /**                                                                                                                                                                         
                             452:     * This is basically a kludge to deal with the now obsolete Label records.  If                                                                                              
                             453:     * you have to read in a sheet that contains Label records, be aware that the rest                                                                                          
                             454:     * of the API doesn't deal with them, the low level structure only provides read-only                                                                                       
                             455:     * semi-immutable structures (the sets are there for interface conformance with NO                                                                                          
                             456:     * Implementation).  In short, you need to call this function passing it a reference                                                                                        
                             457:     * to the Workbook object.  All labels will be converted to LabelSST records and their                                                                                      
                             458:     * contained strings will be written to the Shared String table (SSTRecord) within                                                                                          
                             459:     * the Workbook.                                                                                                                                                            
                             460:     *                                                                                                                                                                          
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>

                             381:        }

                             122:            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Bad requested string length (" + requestedLength + ")");                                                                        
                             123:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             124:        char[] buf;                                                                                                                                                             
                             125:        int availableChars = pIsCompressedEncoding ? ris.remaining() : ris.remaining() / LittleEndianConsts.SHORT_SIZE;                                                         
                             126:        //everything worked out.  Great!                                                                                                                                        
                             127:        if (requestedLength == availableChars) {                                                                                                                                
                             128:            buf = new char[requestedLength];                                                                                                                                    
                             129:        } else {                                                                                                                                                                
                             130:            //sometimes in older Excel 97 .xls files,                                                                                                                           
                             131:            //the requested length is wrong.                                                                                                                                    
                             132:            //Read all available characters.                                                                                                                                    
                             133:            buf = new char[availableChars];                                                                                                                                     
                             134:        }                                                                                                                                                                       
                             ```

                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/util/IOUtils.java:571-577                                                                                                                          
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             571:    public static byte[] safelyAllocate(long length, int maxLength) {                                                                                                           
                             572:        safelyAllocateCheck(length, maxLength);                                                                                                                                 
                             573:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             574:        checkByteSizeLimit(length);                                                                                                                                             
                             575:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             576:        return new byte[(int)length];                                                                                                                                           
                             577:    }                                                                                                                                                                           
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             </code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Root Cause Analysis                                                                                                                                                              
                                - Our original patch targeted RecordInputStream.readStringCommon, but under fuzzing most stringreading actually occurs via FormatRecord.readStringCommon (e.g.,                 
                             inline formula strings) or via UnicodeString  readCompressedUnicode/readUnicodeLEString  readStringCommon.                                                                        
                                - FormatRecord.readStringCommon duplicates the sanitycheck logic but silently truncates when availableChars != requestedLength, so malicious or malformed                       
                             lengths never throw exceptions.                                                                                                                                                     
                                - Even in RecordInputStream.readStringCommon, the hardcoded bounds (00x100000) are never exceeded because incoming lengths come from 16bit headers (065535).                  
                             Thus the sanity check is effectively dead under fuzzing.                                                                                                                            
                             2. Strategy Overview                                                                                                                                                                
                                A. Centralize and unify stringlength validation across all code paths:                                                                                                          
                                    Replace adhoc checks in FormatRecord with the same RecordFormatException.check(...) used in RecordInputStream.                                                             
                                    Enforce a true failfast behavior when requestedLength doesnt match availableChars (rather than silent truncation).                                                      
                                    Leverage HSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength() to drive upper bounds instead of magic 0x100000, so future changes to limits remain in one place.                                
                                B. Harden RecordInputStream.readStringCommon:                                                                                                                                    
                                    Retain or reapply our RecordFormatException.check(requestedLength  0 && requestedLength  max) patch, but switch to using                                                 
                             HSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength().                                                                                                                                                  
                                    Before allocating char[], invoke IOUtils.safelyAllocateCheck(requestedLength, HSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength()), so any oversize request will throw an                     
                             IllegalArgumentException early.                                                                                                                                                     
                                C. Update FormatRecord.readStringCommon:                                                                                                                                         
                                    Remove the if requestedLength  availableChars then shrink buf block.                                                                                                     
                                    Perform the same bounds check via RecordFormatException.check(requestedLength  0 && requestedLength  HSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength(), ).                               
                                    If availableChars < requestedLength, throw RecordFormatException explaining Expected X chars but only saw Y.                                                              
                                    Allocate via IOUtils.safelyAllocateCheck, then read exactly requestedLength characters.                                                                                     
                                D. Ensure UnicodeString deserialization paths benefit from these changes without further modifications; they call through to the improved methods.                               
                             3. Step-by-Step Implementation                                                                                                                                                      
                                1. In RecordInputStream.readStringCommon:                                                                                                                                        
                                   a. Replace the literal 0x100000 with HSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength().                                                                                                     
                                   b. Before `char[] buf = new char[requestedLength];`, call:                                                                                                                    
                                      ```                                                                                                                                                                        
                                      IOUtils.safelyAllocateCheck(requestedLength, HSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength());                                                                                           
                                      ```                                                                                                                                                                        
                                   c. Keep the RecordFormatException.check(...) on the same condition, so failures throw a RecordFormatException.                                                                
                                2. In poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/FormatRecord.java:                                                                                                            
                                   a. Remove lines 120134 (the old sanitycheck and truncation).                                                                                                                
                                   b. Insert at the top of readStringCommon:                                                                                                                                     
                                      ```                                                                                                                                                                        
                                      RecordFormatException.check(                                                                                                                                               
                                          requestedLength >= 0 && requestedLength <= HSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength(),                                                                                          
                                          "Bad requested string length ("+requestedLength+")"                                                                                                                    
                                      );                                                                                                                                                                         
                                      int availableChars = pIsCompressedEncoding                                                                                                                                 
                                          ? ris.remaining()                                                                                                                                                      
                                          : ris.remaining()/LittleEndianConsts.SHORT_SIZE;                                                                                                                       
                                      if (availableChars < requestedLength) {                                                                                                                                    
                                          throw new RecordFormatException(                                                                                                                                       
                                              "Expected to read "+requestedLength+" chars, but only "+availableChars+" available"                                                                                
                                          );                                                                                                                                                                     
                                      }                                                                                                                                                                          
                                      IOUtils.safelyAllocateCheck(requestedLength, HSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength());                                                                                           
                                      char[] buf = new char[requestedLength];                                                                                                                                    
                                      ```                                                                                                                                                                        
                                   c. Proceed with the existing tight loop reading `requestedLength` chars.                                                                                                      
                                   d. Remove any fallback truncation paths.                                                                                                                                      
                                3. Verify that UnicodeStrings calls to `in.readCompressedUnicode(cc)` and `in.readUnicodeLEString(cc)` will now propagate the stricter checks.                                  
                             4. Justification                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - By centralizing bounds validation on HSSFWorkbook.getMaxRecordLength(), we avoid magic constants and keep behavior uniform.                                                    
                                - Switching FormatRecord to failfast ensures malformed lengths injected by the fuzzer lead to a RecordFormatException, which is not swallowed and will                        
                             register as a crash.                                                                                                                                                                
                                - Retaining the full characterreading loop ensures we do not alter legitimate parsing of valid strings.                                                                         
                                - Using IOUtils.safelyAllocateCheck prevents outofmemory or overly large allocations, enforcing a hard upper limit.                                                            
                                - No fuzz harness, test code, or external library is modified; only internal stringparsing logic in core record classes changes.                                                
                             5. Side Effects & Mitigation                                                                                                                                                        
                                - These stricter checks may break Excel files with minor headerlength mismatches that were silently tolerated in FormatRecord. To mitigate, existing production                 
                             code could catch RecordFormatException at a higher level and fall back to truncationbut for fuzzing and security hardening we prefer the crash on invalid state.                   
                                - Regression tests should be run on known .xls samples to ensure no unintended failures. If legitimate files break, consider logging a warning and                               
                             continuingbut for fuzzing we must crash.                                                                                                                                           
                             6. Verification                                                                                                                                                                     
                                - Re-run POIHSSFFuzzer; confirm that malformed length headers now trigger RecordFormatException in both RecordInputStream.readStringCommon and FormatRecord,                     
                             producing a detectable crash.                                                                                                                                                       
                                - Confirm coverage metrics and ensure no other code paths inadvertently swallow the new exceptions.                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             ===Evaluation End===
